## Proposed Changes

### Backend Caching (Phase 2)

#### [NEW] [cacheService.js](file:///C:/Users/anshu/OneDrive/Desktop/TrackPrep/server/src/services/cacheService.js)
Create a unified caching interface. It will check for `REDIS_URL` or `REDIS_HOST`/`REDIS_PORT` env variables and attempt a dynamic import of the `'redis'` client. If not configured or not installed, it falls back to an in-memory `Map` storage with TTL timeouts, enabling cache functionality out-of-the-box.

#### [MODIFY] [problemService.js](file:///C:/Users/anshu/OneDrive/Desktop/TrackPrep/server/src/services/problemService.js)
Integrate `cacheService` inside statistics and listing queries (`getDifficultyStats`, `getTopicStats`, `getTotalCount`). Add cache invalidation calls (`cacheService.clearUserCache(userId)`) on `addProblem`, `updateProblem`, and `deleteProblem`.

#### [MODIFY] [appService.js](file:///C:/Users/anshu/OneDrive/Desktop/TrackPrep/server/src/services/appService.js)
Integrate `cacheService` in stats queries (`getStatusStats`, `getTotalCount`). Invalidate cache on mutations (`addApplication`, `updateApplication`, `deleteApplication`).

#### [MODIFY] [taskService.js](file:///C:/Users/anshu/OneDrive/Desktop/TrackPrep/server/src/services/taskService.js)
Integrate caching for pending counts (`getPendingCount`) and invalidate cache on mutations (`addTask`, `updateTask`, `deleteTask`).

