### Frontend Real-time UI (Phase 3)

#### [NEW] [socket.js](file:///C:/Users/anshu/OneDrive/Desktop/TrackPrep/client/src/services/socket.js)
A client-side socket helper that dynamically checks for `'socket.io-client'`. If not present, it loads a Mock Socket implementation that supports local events/callbacks (facilitating mockup simulations and previewing the live feed). If present, it connects to the backend Socket.io server. Includes a `useSocket()` hook.

#### [MODIFY] [Dashboard.jsx](file:///C:/Users/anshu/OneDrive/Desktop/TrackPrep/client/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx)
Integrate the Live Activity Feed and Study Groups (Rooms) visual components below the analytics charts. Bind them to socket events:
1. `live_activity` - Appends real-time notifications to the live feed.
2. `join_room` / `leave_room` - Permits entering a study group chat room.
Includes simulation features that display simulated peer activity updates if real Socket.io clients aren't installed/active.

